Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from the fridge to bring them up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Red Wine Jus ==

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the jus{150%ml} into a small #saucepan, bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{15%grams}, then reduce the heat to medium-high.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once thickened to your liking, remove from the heat.

== Steaks ==

About 10 mins before the chips are ready, season the steaks with @salt{to taste}.

Tip the @cracked black pepper{2%sachets} onto a large #plate, then lay the steaks into it.

Turn the steaks in the pepper until evenly coated, pressing down firmly to ensure it sticks.

> TIP: Brush off some pepper if needed - it has some heat!

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side. Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a clean #cutting board{}, cover with #foil and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, thinly slice the steaks and transfer to your plates. Reheat the red wine jus and pour it over the steaks.

Sprinkle the @truffle zest{1%sachet} over the chips, toss together, then share between your plates.

Serve the @wild rocket{40%grams} alongside and finish by drizzling the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the leaves.

Enjoy!